parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to a increased risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle falls apart
the buckle jams into the latch
the latch does not lock
the buckle is hard to insert
the metal tongue is difficult to insert into the buckle
the seat belt does not retract
the seat belt comes unlatched at times.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to a increased risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt will not retract into its assembly
the shoulder belt will not retract
the seat belt is rendered inoperative.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexpected deflation of a motorcycle tire due to sidewall failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Rapid tire deflation
tire blowout
sidewall cracks
tire failure while riding or while parked.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An engine compartment fire can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to a total loss, and poses a risk to the safety of the occupants and bystanders.
symptoms: Flames or smoke visible from the engine compartment
burning smell
melting of plastic components
warping of metal components
electrical system failure
loss of power
difficulty steering or braking.
